  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3e1cd92da80c7495a8fe7eb91fa80c2f, type: 3}
  m_Name: Bamboo
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Plants.PlantData
  displayName: Bamboo
  audioClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 288a39f1324be4843988867d2449a118, type: 3}
  environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  environmentLayers: []
  environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  poem:
    text: "In Wuqian, Visit a Buddhist Monk's Green Bamboo Pavillion\n\nOne may do
      without meat in one\u2019s diet, \nBut one cannot live without bamboo. \nWithout
      meat, one grows thin; \nWithout bamboo, one grows vulgar. \nA thin man may
      regain his weight, \nBut a vulgar man cannot be cured. \nOthers may laugh at
      these words, \nFinding them both lofty and foolish. \nIf, in the presence of
      this gentleman, one still feasts heartily, \nHow could there ever be a Yangzhou
      Crane in this world?\n\nSu Dongpo"
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  contextInfos:
  - text: 'In Chinese literari tradition, bamboo is held as a model of a gentleman.
      The stem grows straight and does not break under pressure, signaling tenacity. '
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: 'The Leaves droop, almost like their bowing and it does not bloom, symbolising
      modesty. And its core is hollow, like it''s kepping an open heart.

'
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
